The paper deals with the concept of Kolmogorov complexity, which is a fundamental concept in computational complexity theory (cs.CC). The paper also discusses the slow growth law, which is a property of complexity measures (cs.IT). The paper proposes a new notion of depth for sets of strings, which is related to the concept of randomness (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the properties of random and non-random sequences, which is related to cryptography (cs.CR). Finally, the paper discusses the existence of deep sets, which is related to machine learning and data analysis (cs.LG).
